# JavaScript – Browser Storage & Useful Browser APIs

---

## 💾 localStorage

Stores data **persistently** in the browser — survives page reloads and tab/browser closes. Max ~5MB. Strings only.

```js
// Store
localStorage.setItem("username", "Ali");
localStorage.setItem("theme", "dark");

// Retrieve
const name  = localStorage.getItem("username");  // "Ali"
const theme = localStorage.getItem("theme");      // "dark"
const missing = localStorage.getItem("xyz");      // null

// Remove one
localStorage.removeItem("theme");

// Clear all
localStorage.clear();

// Length
localStorage.length;
```

### Storing Objects (must JSON-serialize)
```js
const user = { name: "Ali", age: 25 };

// Save
localStorage.setItem("user", JSON.stringify(user));

// Retrieve
const stored = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem("user"));
console.log(stored.name);  // "Ali"

// Safe retrieve helper
function getItem(key) {
  try {
    return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(key));
  } catch {
    return null;
  }
}
```

---

## 🕐 sessionStorage

Same API as `localStorage`, but data is **cleared when the tab is closed**.

```js
sessionStorage.setItem("token", "abc123");
sessionStorage.getItem("token");
sessionStorage.removeItem("token");
sessionStorage.clear();
```

---

## localStorage vs sessionStorage vs Cookies

| Feature | localStorage | sessionStorage | Cookies |
|---------|-------------|----------------|---------|
| Capacity | ~5MB | ~5MB | ~4KB |
| Expires | Never | Tab close | Set by developer |
| Sent to server | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ (every request) |
| Accessible in JS | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Use case | User prefs, cache | Temp session data | Auth tokens, server |

